President Donald Trump has announced his intent to nominate Michael Eric Wooten as the Administrator for Federal Procurement Policy, Office of Management and Budget. Wooten is currently a senior advisor for acquisitions at the Department of Educationâ€™s Federal Student Aid office and has previously served in the Trump Administration as acting Assistant Secretary and Deputy Assistant Secretary for Career, Technical, and Adult Education. He holds a doctorate in Higher Education Management and has experience in contract management. 

In addition, President Trump has announced his intent to appoint several individuals to key positions in his Administration. Robert F. Bozzuto III is set to be appointed as an Assistant Secretary of Labor (Public Affairs). He currently serves as the White House Liaison at the Department of Labor. Jonathan Warren Burkan, Sam Devinki, David Michael Flaum, and Jeremey Halpern are set to be appointed as Members of the United States Holocaust Memorial Council for the remainder of a five-year term.